sentences: Dirk, Knight Brossé (born 18 February 1960, Ghent) is a Belgian conductor and composer.
His score for the BBC/HBO series Parade's End (2012) was nominated for an Emmy Award.
In 2008, he made his first appearance at the Royal Albert Hall in London, conducting the London Symphony Orchestra.
In 2010, at the request of the Hong Kong Chinese Orchestra, he wrote The Hallow-e'en Dances.
In 2010, Dirk Brossé was made an honorary citizen of Destelbergen.
In 2013, he was elevated to Belgium's hereditary nobility, with the personal title of Ridder.
In 2001 he started working with The Rotterdam Philharmonic Orchestra, The London Symphony Orchestra and The KBS Symphonic Orchestra of Seoul.
section: == Work as conductor ==

sentences: In 2009 he started his work with Star Wars: In Concert.
section: == Work as conductor ==

sentences: In 2008 and 2009 he had guest appearances in The Chamber Orchestra of Philadelphia, where he later debuted as musical director in 2010, succeeding Ignat Solzhenitsyn.

sentences: Among his 20 distinctive film scores for award-winning films are "Daens" (Academy Award nomination 1993), "When the Light Comes", "A Peasant's Psalm", "Marie" (Nominated Overall Winner in the French Film Section at the Venice Film Festival in 1994) and the classic silent film "Visages d'Enfants".

sentences: Dirk Brossé added a new dimension to the wide range of his oeuvre with his scoring of the musical "Sacco & Vanzetti" commissioned by the Theatre of the Royal Ballet of Flanders in 1996.
section: == Film and musical works ==

sentences: Brossé wrote also the score for the musical based on the world-famous cartoon character "Tintin" created by Hergé, which premiered in September 2001 in Belgium.
section: == Film and musical works ==

sentences: In 1999 Brossé was invited by the City Council of Shanghai, to conduct the Shanghai Philharmonic Orchestra in performances marking the 50th Anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
